    // IDPAD-3523 - this block must come BEFORE footer external JS files (litFooterJS)
    // need setCookie() and getCookie() functions declared earlier for internal testing
    // this block is only necessary for internal testing
    function setCookie(c_name, value, expiredays) {
        var exdate = new Date();
        exdate.setDate(exdate.getDate() + expiredays);
        if (expiredays == 0) {
            document.cookie = c_name + "=" + escape(value) + ";path=/";
        } else {
            document.cookie = c_name + "=" + escape(value) +
         ((expiredays == null) ? "" : ";expires=" + exdate.toGMTString()) + ";path=/";
        }
    }

    function getCookie(c_name) {
        if (document.cookie.length > 0) {
            var arrCookieValues = document.cookie.split('; ');
            for (var i = 0; i < arrCookieValues.length; i++) {
                var arrCookieValuePair = arrCookieValues[i].split('=');
                if (arrCookieValuePair[0] === c_name) {
                    var retval = arrCookieValues[i].substring(arrCookieValuePair[0].length + 1, arrCookieValues[i].length);
                    return unescape(retval);
                }
            }
        }
        return '';
    }

    if (window.location.href.toLowerCase().indexOf('mobile=true') > -1 || getCookie('ismobile') === 'true') {
        setCookie('ismobile','true',0);
        $("body").attr("mobile", "true");
    } 
    
    function waitToRemoveStylesheet(recursion) {
        if ($('#optimizelyFosMobile').length > 0) {
            $('#optimizelyFosMobile').attr('disabled','disabled').remove();
            return true;
        } else {
            recursion++;
            setTimeout(function() { waitToRemoveStylesheet(recursion) },1);
        }
    }

    if (window.location.href.toLowerCase().indexOf('mobile=false') > -1  || getCookie('ismobile') === 'false') {
        setCookie('ismobile','false',0);
        $("body").attr("mobile", "false");
        waitToRemoveStylesheet(0);
        $("form").css("display", "initial");
    }

    // END IDPAD-3523
</script>

    // 11/22/2016 JW - IDPAD-3191
    var five9CallRecording = (function () {
        var stopCookieName = 'five9CallRecordingStopped';
        var redirectCookieName = 'five9RedirectUrl';
        var errorCookieName = 'five9Error';
        var cookieDomain = 'philips.factoryoutletstore.com';
        var stopCookieLife = 5; // Minutes
        var retryLimit = 1;
        var retryCount = 0;

        function getUrlParameters(name) {
            name = name.replace(/[\[]/, '\\[').replace(/[\]]/, '\\]');
            var regex = new RegExp('[\\?&]' + name + '=([^&#]*)');
            var results = regex.exec(location.search);
            return results === null ? null : decodeURIComponent(results[1].replace(/\+/g, ' '));
        }

        function getCookie(name) {
            var reg = new RegExp('(?:^|;\\s?)' + name + '=([^;]*)', 'i');
            var matches = reg.exec(document.cookie);
            
            return (matches && matches.length == 2 ? matches[1] : null);
        }

        function setCookie(name, value, expireInMinutes) {
            var expirationDate = new Date();
            expirationDate.setMinutes(expirationDate.getMinutes() + expireInMinutes);

            document.cookie = name + '=' + value 
                + ';domain=' + cookieDomain
                + ';path=/'
                + ';expires=' + expirationDate.toUTCString();
        }

        function removeCookie(name) {
            setCookie(name, '', -1);
        }

        var CTIWS_URL = 'http://localhost:8080/agent/v2';

        // Resumes call recording
        function resumeRecording() {
            recordCall(true);
        }

        // Pauses call recording
        function pauseRecording() {
            recordCall(false);
        }

        /** Record call API call
            * @param {boolean} flag True to record, false to pause
            */
        function recordCall(flag) {
            var post = '<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:urn="urn:core_v2.agent.api.five9.com">'
                + '<soapenv:Header/>'
                + '<soapenv:Body>'
                + '<urn:recordCall>'
                + '<flag>' + flag + '</flag>'
                + '</urn:recordCall>'
                + '</soapenv:Body>'
                + '</soapenv:Envelope>';

            var headers = {
                SOAPAction: '',
                Accept: 'application/xml',
                "Content-Type": 'text/xml'
            };

            var callbackfn = function () {
                var parser = new DOMParser();
                var responseXML = parser.parseFromString(this.responseText, "text/xml");
                var result = (responseXML.getElementsByTagName("emptyResponse").length ? true : false);

                if (!result) {
                    if (retryCount < retryLimit) {
                        retryCount++;
                        recordCall(flag);
                        return false;
                    }

                    var errorMessage = null;
                    if (!this.responseText) {
                        errorMessage = "Cannot connect";
                    } 
                    else {
                        var faultTag = responseXML.getElementsByTagName("faultstring");
                        if (faultTag.length) {
                            errorMessage = faultTag[0].textContent;
                            setCookie(errorCookieName, errorMessage, 1);
                            //throw new Error(errorMessage);
                        } else {
                            var returnValue = responseXML.getElementsByTagName("return");
                            if (returnValue.length) {
                                errorMessage = returnValue[0].textContent;
                            }
                        }
                    }

                    if (errorMessage) {
                        setCookie(errorCookieName, errorMessage, 1);
                    }
                }

                if (!flag && result) {
                    setCookie(stopCookieName, 1, stopCookieLife);
                } else if (flag) {
                    removeCookie(stopCookieName);
                }

                var redirectURL = getCookie(redirectCookieName);
                if (redirectURL) {
                    window.location.replace(redirectURL);
                }
            };

            sendRequest(CTIWS_URL, post, headers, callbackfn);
        }

        /**
            * Generic xml http request sending method
            *
            * @param url Server address, including query string
            * @param post The post data, or undefined for GET
            * @param headers Object with headers key-value pairs
            * @param callbackfn A callback function reference
            * @returns xmlhttp request object
            */
        function sendRequest(url, post, headers, callbackfn) {

            var isXDR = false;
            var url2 = url.toLowerCase();
            if (url2.indexOf('http') == 0) {
                var parts = url2.split('/');
                var hostport = (parts.length >= 3 ? parts[2] : '');
                isXDR = (hostport != location.host.toLowerCase());
                parts = null;
                hostport = null;
            }
            url2 = null;

            var method = (post == undefined ? 'GET' : 'POST');
            var xmlhttp = createXMLHttpRequest(isXDR);
            xmlhttp.onerror = callbackfn;
            xmlhttp.open(method, url, true);

            if ('readyState' in xmlhttp) { // XMLHttpRequest
                if (headers) {
                    for (var key in headers) {
                        if (!headers.hasOwnProperty(key)) continue;
                        xmlhttp.setRequestHeader(key, headers[key]);
                    }
                }
                // set X-Requested-With on same-origin XMLHttpRequests only
                if (!isXDR && (!headers || !headers['X-Requested-With'])) {
                    xmlhttp.setRequestHeader('X-Requested-With', 'XMLHttpRequest');
                }
                // set Content-Type on POSTs using XMLHttpRequest
                if ('setRequestHeader' in xmlhttp
                    && method.toUpperCase() == 'POST'
                    && (!headers || !headers['Content-Type'])) {
                    xmlhttp.setRequestHeader('Content-Type', 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded');
                }

                xmlhttp.onreadystatechange = function () {
                    if (this.readyState == 4) {
                        try {
                            if (typeof callbackfn == 'function') {
                                callbackfn.call(this);
                            }
                        } catch (e) {
                        }
                    }
                };
            } else { // XDomainRequest
                xmlhttp.onprogress = function () { };
                var fn = function () {
                    try {
                        if (typeof callbackfn == 'function') {
                            callbackfn.call(this);
                        }
                    } catch (e) {
                    }
                };
                xmlhttp.onload = fn;
                xmlhttp.onerror = fn;
                xmlhttp.ontimeout = fn;
            }

            xmlhttp.send(post);

            return xmlhttp;
        }

        /**
            * Creates a browser-specific XMLHttpRequest
            *
            * @param isXDR True if the request will be cross-domain (IE-specific)
            * @returns {XMLHttpRequest}
            */
        function createXMLHttpRequest(isXDR) {
            var isIE8or9 = /MSIE 8|MSIE 9/.test(navigator.userAgent);
            if (isXDR && isIE8or9) {
                try {
                    // XDR is IE8,9 specific, otherwise use XHR
                    return new XDomainRequest();
                } catch (e) { }
            }

            try {
                return new XMLHttpRequest();
            } catch (e) { }

            try {
                return window.createRequest();
            } catch (e) { }

            try {
                return new ActiveXObject('Msxml2.XMLHTTP');
            } catch (e) { }

            try {
                return new ActiveXObject('Microsoft.XMLHTTP');
            } catch (e) { }
        }

        // Public Methods
        return {
            pauseRecording: pauseRecording,
            resumeRecording: resumeRecording,
            setStopCheck: function () {
                window.onfocus = function () {
                    var stopCookie = getCookie(stopCookieName);
                    if (!stopCookie) {
                        location.reload();
                    } else {
                        setCookie(stopCookieName, stopCookie, stopCookieLife);
                    }
                }
            },
            init: function (pause) {
                var stopCookie = getCookie(stopCookieName);
                if (pause && !stopCookie) {
                    pauseRecording();
                } else if (!pause && stopCookie) {
                    resumeRecording();
                }
            }
        }

    })();

                if (host == undefined) {
                    host = window.document.location.host;
                }
                if ((host != undefined) && (host != '') && (host != null)) {
                    var values = host.split('.');
                    if (values.length > 0) {
                        var domain = '.' + values[1] + '.' + values[2];
                    }
                }
                if (days != null) {
                    var date = new Date();
                    date.setTime(date.getTime() + (days * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
                    var expires = "; expires=" + date.toGMTString();
                }
                else {
                    var expires = "";
                }
                document.cookie = name + "=" + value + expires + "; path=/;" + "domain=" + domain;
            }
            function readCookie(name) {
                var nameEQ = name + "=";
                var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
                for (var i = 0; i < ca.length; i++) {
                    var c = ca[i];
                    while (c.charAt(0) == ' ') c = c.substring(1, c.length);
                    if (c.indexOf(nameEQ) == 0) return c.substring(nameEQ.length, c.length);
